Early Wednesday morning, while most of America slept, Marcello helped a family say their final goodbye to their father over FaceTime.
“We love you and we forgive you for anything,” she described the family members saying to their father.
At 1 a.m. on Wednesday, she held up a FaceTime call to help a family say their final goodbye to their father.
But due to the pandemic, Marcello has been working five days a week and caring for four ventilated patients at a time.
She expressed sadness that the pandemic limits the TLC (tender loving care) that nurses wish to show their patients.